&lt;div class="hero-content"&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;PACE-UP FULL PHD SCHOLARSHIP 2026‚Äì2030&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;p class="hero-subtitle"&gt;Opportunity to pursue a PhD in Infectious Diseases, Epidemiology, Global Health, and Antimicrobial Resistance in Germany&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;!-- Button with scholarship deadline --&gt;
  &lt;a 
    href="mailto:salome.steinke@vgcare.org"
    target="_blank"
    class="apply-button"
    data-deadline="2025-10-31T23:59:00"
  &gt;
    APPLY NOW
  &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;div class="main-content"&gt;
  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The BIODAS Team&lt;/strong&gt; is pleased to share information about the &lt;strong&gt;PACE-UP Full PhD Scholarship 2026‚Äì2030&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì a prestigious scholarship program funded by &lt;strong&gt;DAAD&lt;/strong&gt;, offering research and doctoral training opportunities at leading German universities in the fields of &lt;strong&gt;infectious diseases, epidemiology, global health, and antimicrobial resistance&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PACE-UP (PAN ASEAN Coalition for Epidemic and Outbreak Preparedness)&lt;/strong&gt; is a global health initiative coordinated by the &lt;strong&gt;Vietnamese-German Center for Medical Research (VG-CARE), 108 Military Central Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;, in collaboration with partners in Germany, Malaysia, Indonesia, and other countries to enhance epidemic preparedness and strengthen health response capabilities in the Southeast Asian region.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Official website:&lt;/strong&gt; 
    &lt;a href="https://paceup.org/opportunities/" target="_blank"&gt;https://paceup.org/opportunities/&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;!-- Illustration --&gt;
  &lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;div class="img-wrap"&gt;
      &lt;img src="https://i0.wp.com/paceup.org/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/Call-for-PhD-Applications_VG-CARE_Final-1.jpg?resize=768%2C1109" class="img" /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;figcaption&gt;
      Image: Call for PhD Applications (Source: PACE-UP)
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;1. Program Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;The program is recruiting for &lt;strong&gt;fully funded PhD positions&lt;/strong&gt; in the fields of &lt;strong&gt;infectious diseases, epidemiology, global health, and antimicrobial resistance&lt;/strong&gt; at leading research institutions in Germany, within the framework of the DAAD-funded PACE-UP project.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;PhD students will be based at one of four leading institutions: the &lt;strong&gt;University of T√ºbingen&lt;/strong&gt;, the &lt;strong&gt;University of L√ºbeck&lt;/strong&gt;, the &lt;strong&gt;University of Hamburg&lt;/strong&gt;, or in collaboration with the &lt;strong&gt;Heidelberg Institute of Global Health&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;2. Program Benefits&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;üéì 4-year full scholarship (07/2026 ‚Äì 06/2030).&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;üí∂ Monthly stipend of ‚Ç¨1,400, health insurance, and a round-trip air ticket.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;üî¨ Access to modern research facilities and infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;üåç Opportunity to participate in international exchanges, fieldwork, and scientific conferences.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;üë©‚Äçüî¨ Guidance and supervision in a dynamic, interdisciplinary international research environment.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- Illustration --&gt;
  &lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;div class="img-wrap"&gt;
      &lt;img src="https://uni-tuebingen.de/fileadmin/Uni_Tuebingen/Fakultaeten/WiSo/Wiwi/Uploads/International/Neue_Aula_092.jpg" class="img" /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;figcaption&gt;
      Image: Universit√§t T√ºbingen (Source: https://uni-tuebingen.de)
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;


  &lt;h2&gt;3. Application Requirements&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;The program welcomes applicants from all academic backgrounds, with selection criteria based on merit and academic achievement. First-generation students and underrepresented groups in scientific research are encouraged to apply.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Master's degree or Medical Doctor with a Master's degree in Health Sciences, Public Health, Pharmacy, Biology, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Excellent academic record and a clear research orientation.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Proficiency in English (spoken and written, equivalent to IELTS ‚â• 6.5).&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Ability to read and analyze scientific literature.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Basic laboratory skills and adherence to good laboratory practice standards.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;4. Application Instructions&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Applicants should submit &lt;strong&gt;one PDF file in English&lt;/strong&gt; containing the following documents:&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;CV (max. 2 pages).&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Statement of Purpose (max. 1 page).&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Degrees and academic transcripts.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;English language certificate (TOEFL / IELTS / TOEIC or equivalent, minimum IELTS 6.5).&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Names and contact information of 2 academic referees.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ol&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;5. Important Timeline&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;div class="timeline-flow"&gt;
    &lt;div class="timeline-item"&gt;
      &lt;span class="timeline-date"&gt;10/31/2025&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Application deadline&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="timeline-item"&gt;
      &lt;span class="timeline-date"&gt;Late 2025&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Pre-selection interviews by the VG-CARE Scientific Committee&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="timeline-item"&gt;
      &lt;span class="timeline-date"&gt;Early 2026&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Online interviews with DAAD and representatives of German universities&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="timeline-item"&gt;
      &lt;span class="timeline-date"&gt;Mid-2026&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Final results announced&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="timeline-item"&gt;
      &lt;span class="timeline-date"&gt;07/01/2026&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Program officially begins&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="final-note"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Application deadline: 10/31/2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
    üìß Submit applications to: &lt;a href="mailto:salome.steinke@vgcare.org"&gt;salome.steinke@vgcare.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;
    Contact person: &lt;strong&gt;Ms. Salome Steinke (VG-CARE)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;
    Phone: +84 984 684 908&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="final-note"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Start preparing today!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
    PACE-UP is not just a scholarship ‚Äì it's an opportunity to become a global scientist, contributing to medicine, public health, and epidemic preparedness in the future.&lt;br&gt;
