&lt;div class="hero-content"&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;CHEVENING FULLY FUNDED SCHOLARSHIP 2025/2026&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;p class="hero-subtitle"&gt;Study in the UK for young global leaders&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;!-- Button with scholarship deadline --&gt;
  &lt;a 
    href="https://www.chevening.org/apply"
    target="_blank"
    class="apply-button"
    data-deadline="2025-10-07T23:59:00"
  &gt;
    APPLY NOW
  &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;div class="main-content"&gt;
  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The BIODAS Team&lt;/strong&gt; is pleased to share information about the &lt;strong&gt;Chevening Scholarship&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì the UK government's prestigious scholarship program for outstanding individuals with a desire to create positive change in their communities, countries, and globally. This is an opportunity to study for a one-year master's degree in the UK completely free of charge, opening up a journey of academic and professional development and a sustainable international leadership network.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;div style="text-align:center;"&gt;
    &lt;iframe 
      src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/hHDTKvt4yIY?si=7aA_ddT_g6sWoywN"
      title="YouTube video player"
      style="width:auto; height:auto; aspect-ratio:16/9; border:0;"
      allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
      referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
      allowfullscreen&gt;
    &lt;/iframe&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;strong&gt;Official website:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.chevening.org" target="_blank"&gt;https://www.chevening.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;1. Introduction to the Chevening Scholarship&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Chevening Scholarships enable promising young leaders from around the world to pursue a one-year master's degree at leading universities in the UK. If you have passion, influence, and a desire to solve local or global challenges, Chevening is the opportunity for you.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Professional and academic development.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Expand your international network.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Experience British culture.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Build a long-lasting cooperative relationship with the UK.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;!-- Illustration --&gt;
  &lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;div class="img-wrap"&gt;
      &lt;img src="https://www.scholarshipregion.com/wp-content/uploads/elementor/thumbs/UK-Government-Chevening-Scholarships-qc0g3ibu1s0523zq02df7ib6anvlhihenpt574hz4w.jpg" class="img" /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;figcaption&gt;
      Illustration (Source: www.scholarshipregion.com)
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;2. Who can apply for the Chevening Scholarship?&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Chevening does not have any restrictions on age, gender, religion, marital status, or profession. What matters is your leadership mindset, clear goals, and potential to make a positive impact.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;h3&gt;‚úÖ Eligibility requirements:&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Be a citizen of an eligible country.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Commit to returning to your home country for at least 2 years after the scholarship ends.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Have at least 2,800 hours of work experience.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Have a bachelor's degree that qualifies you for a master's degree in the UK.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Apply for 3 different courses and have at least 1 unconditional offer of admission.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;h3&gt;‚ùå Not eligible if:&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Have British or dual British citizenship.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Have previously studied in the UK with another UK government scholarship.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Are an employee or relative of a UK government agency in the last 2 years.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;3. Work experience&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Applicants need at least 2,800 hours of work experience (equivalent to 2 years full-time), which can be calculated from:&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Full-time or part-time employment.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Volunteer activities.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Paid or unpaid internships.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;4. Chevening Application Guide&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ol&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Check your eligibility.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Choose 3 master's courses in the UK.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Prepare your application and letters of recommendation.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Apply online through the Chevening system.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Attend an interview and submit an unconditional offer of admission.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ol&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;5. Preparing for the Chevening interview&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Prepare thoroughly: master the content of your application, your career orientation, and demonstrate your leadership ability and confident English communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;6. Choosing a course in the UK&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Applicants need to choose 3 eligible master's programs from universities in the UK.&lt;br&gt;
  &lt;a href="https://www.chevening.org/scholarships/find-a-course/" target="_blank"&gt;Find a suitable course (Chevening Course Finder)&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;7. Improving English skills&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Although Chevening does not require an English language certificate when applying, most UK universities do. Hone your skills to write better essays and perform better in interviews.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;!-- Illustration --&gt;
  &lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;div class="img-wrap"&gt;
      &lt;img src="https://asean.org/wp-content/uploads/elementor/thumbs/Chevening-pic1724738642-scaled-qt9q5iek65l9u60mnz6mswzdf7322vdce2z1lqj2iw.jpeg" class="img" /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;figcaption&gt;
      Illustration (Source: https://asean.org/)
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;8. Important timeline&lt;/h2&gt;

  &lt;div class="timeline-flow"&gt;
    &lt;div class="timeline-item"&gt;
      &lt;span class="timeline-date"&gt;08/05/2025&lt;/span&gt;
      &lt;p&gt;Application portal opens&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="timeline-item"&gt;
      &lt;span class="timeline-date"&gt;10/07/2025&lt;/span&gt;
