&lt;div class="hero-content"&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;EUROPUBHEALTH+ FULLY FUNDED MASTER'S SCHOLARSHIP&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;p class="hero-subtitle"&gt;A Master's program in Public Health in 2‚Äì3 European countries with a full Erasmus Mundus scholarship&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;!-- Button with scholarship deadline --&gt;
  &lt;a 
    href="https://www.europubhealth.org"
    target="_blank"
    class="apply-button"
    data-deadline="2026-01-08T12:00:00"
  &gt;
    APPLY NOW
  &lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



&lt;div class="main-content"&gt;
  &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The BIODAS Team&lt;/strong&gt; is pleased to introduce the &lt;strong&gt;Erasmus Mundus Europubhealth+ Scholarship&lt;/strong&gt; ‚Äì a fully-funded master's program in Public Health for international students, allowing them to study in 2‚Äì3 European countries, receive a dual degree from 2 leading universities, and receive financial support of ‚Ç¨1,400/month. Notably, the program accepts students from other fields ‚Äì whether you have a background in Medicine, Pharmacy, Biotechnology, or Economics, Law, or Sociology, you can apply.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Official website:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.europubhealth.org" target="_blank"&gt;https://www.europubhealth.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;!-- Illustration --&gt;
  &lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;div class="img-wrap"&gt;
      &lt;img src="https://www.europubhealth.org/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/Logos-2024-2025-2048x410.png.webp" class="img" /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;figcaption&gt;Illustration (Source: www.europubhealth.org)&lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;1. Introduction to the Europubhealth+ program&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Europubhealth+&lt;/strong&gt; is a 2-year (120 ECTS) Erasmus Mundus Master's program in Public Health, recognized by the European Commission as a "Master of Excellence" since 2006. The program is taught by a consortium of 8 leading European universities, offering students the opportunity to study in multiple countries and receive a globally recognized dual degree.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;The program welcomes international students with a Bachelor's degree (minimum 180 ECTS) or equivalent, from all academic fields:&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Health sciences: Medicine, Pharmacy, Biology, Nursing, Biomedical Engineering...&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Social sciences: Sociology, Economics, Law, Political Science, Anthropology...&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Business administration and related fields.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;Objective: To train multidisciplinary professionals who can analyze and address public health challenges on a global scale, and propose and implement evidence-based policies to improve public health.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;2. Why choose Europubhealth+&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;‚úÖ Full scholarship: ‚Ç¨1,400/month + tuition fee waiver + health insurance&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;‚úÖ Dual degree from 2 EU universities, internationally recognized&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;‚úÖ Study in 2‚Äì3 European countries, a unique multicultural experience&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;‚úÖ Accepts students from other fields ‚Äì no medical background required&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;‚úÖ Includes biostatistics, epidemiology, health policy, health economics&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;‚úÖ Global alumni network in public health&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;3. Study pathway&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Year 1:&lt;/strong&gt; Foundational knowledge of Public Health (60 ECTS)&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;p&gt;Students choose to study at 1 of the following 4 universities:&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;University of Sheffield ‚Äì UK (English)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;University College Dublin ‚Äì Ireland (English)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;University of Granada ‚Äì Spain (Spanish)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;University of Li√®ge ‚Äì Belgium (French)&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Year 2:&lt;/strong&gt; Specialization and Practice (60 ECTS)&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Maastricht University ‚Äì Netherlands (English)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Jagiellonian University ‚Äì Poland (English)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;EHESP School of Public Health ‚Äì France (Rennes)&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;University of Bordeaux ISPED ‚Äì France (Bordeaux)&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;p&gt;The content includes specialized modules, an internship (2‚Äì6 months), and a master's thesis.&lt;/p&gt;

  &lt;!-- Illustration --&gt;
  &lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;div class="img-wrap"&gt;
      &lt;img src="https://pbs.twimg.com/media/GaAArEWXcAArfol.jpg" class="img" /&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;figcaption&gt;Illustration (Source: Internet)&lt;/figcaption&gt;
  &lt;/figure&gt;

  &lt;h2&gt;4. Admission requirements&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;div class="highlight-box"&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Bachelor's degree ‚â•180 ECTS in any field.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;No medical background required.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;IELTS ‚â•6.5 or equivalent (depending on the pathway).&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Application documents: degree & transcript, CV, motivation letter, 2 letters of recommendation, language certificate.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ul&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

